text: Dino Skender (born 10 December 1983) is a Croatian professional football manager who is the head coach of Slovenian Prva Liga club Olimpija Ljubljana. ==Managerial career== Skender started his managerial career at age 34, as the head coach of the second team of NK Osijek in the Croatian Second Football League. On 30 March 2019, following the departure of Zoran Zekić, he was appointed the head coach of the first team. Skender was fired from Osijek on 21 September 2019.
